Last Question Solution :
public static int sumAtKthLevel(Node root,int k)
{
int sum=0,c=1;
Queue<Node> q=new LinkedList<>();
q.add(root);
q.add(null);
while(c<=k)
{
Node current=q.poll();
if(current==null)
{
c++;
if(q.isEmpty())
{
return sum;
}
else
{
q.add(null);
}
}
else
{
if(k==c)
sum+=current.data;
else
{
if(current.left!=null)
q.add(current.left);
if(current.right!=null)
q.add(current.right);
}
}
}
return sum;
}

Name: Raushan Paswan
Comment:
Dear Shraddha Didi, you're doing a mistake in finding the height of the tree. Because in a tree, the height of any node is the number of edges from the leaf node to that node in the longest path. And the height of the root node is known as the height of the tree. If we have no node then the height of the tree is -1 and If we have a single node then the height is 0.
Code:
public static int height(Node root){
if(root==null){
return -1;
}

int leftnode=height(root.left);
int rightnode=height(root.right);

return Math.max(leftnode,rightnode)+1;
}

Homework Problem:
int sumOfKthLevel(Node* root, int k) {
if(root == nullptr) {
return -1;
}

std::queue<Node*> queue;
queue.push(root);
queue.push(nullptr);

int n = 1;
int sum = 0;

while (!queue.empty())
{
Node* node = queue.front();
queue.pop();

if(node == nullptr) {
if(queue.empty()) {
break;
}
else {
n++;
queue.push(nullptr);
}
}
else {
if(n == k) {
sum += node->data;
}

if(node->left != nullptr) {
queue.push(node->left);
}

if(node->right != nullptr) {
queue.push(node->right);
}
}
}

return sum;
}

Name: Shailesh Kumar

//Solution of Last Question(Sum of nodes at Kth level)

import java.util.LinkedList;
import java.util.Queue;

class MyTree{
static class Node{
int data;
Node left;
Node right;
Node(int data){
this.data=data;
left=null;
right=null;
}
}
static class BinaryTree{
int idx=-1;
Node buildTree(int[] nodes){
idx++;
if(nodes[idx]==-1)
return null;
Node node=new Node(nodes[idx]);
node.left=buildTree(nodes);
node.right=buildTree(nodes);
return node;
}
}
static int sumOfNodesAtKthLevel(Node root, int k){
int sum=0;
int level=1;
if(root==null)
return 0;
Queue<Node> queue=new LinkedList<>();
queue.add(root);
queue.add(null);
while(!queue.isEmpty()){
Node currNode=queue.remove();
if(currNode==null){
level++;
if(queue.isEmpty())
break;
else
queue.add(null);
}
else{
if(level==k)
sum+= currNode.data;
if(currNode.left!=null)
queue.add(currNode.left);
if(currNode.right!=null)
queue.add(currNode.right);
}
}
return sum;
}
public static void main(String[] args) {
int[] nodes ={1,2,4,-1,-1,5,-1,-1,3,-1,6,-1,-1};
BinaryTree tree= new BinaryTree();
Node root= tree.buildTree(nodes);
int k=3;
int sum=sumOfNodesAtKthLevel(root, k);
System.out.println("Sum = "+sum);
}
}
